    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> are the files which are in the _ignore_ field of the tsconfig still needed to be there now that it's listed as a dependency @eunjae-lee ?\r\n\r\n@Haroenv \r\nFor example, at `test/mock/createInsightsClient.ts`, it imports files directly from search-insights\r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport AlgoliaAnalytics from 'search-insights/lib/insights';\r\nimport { processQueue } from 'search-insights/lib/_processQueue';\r\nimport { getFunctionalInterface } from 'search-insights/lib/_getFunctionalInterface';\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/test/mock/createInsightsClient.ts#L1:L4\r\n\r\nTo clean up `exclude` at tsconfig, we should either\r\n\r\n1. export them from search-insights and import them properly in those files\r\nor\r\n2. search-insights gets the same linting rules and makes no trouble within InstantSearch.js code",
